    .reveal
      .slides
        section.title(data-background-size="300px")
          h1 Static Single Page Web Apps
          h3 The Good, the Bad, and the Ugly
          p
            small David Von Lehman / <a href="http://twitter.com/davidvlsea">@davidvlsea</a> / david@aerobatic.io

        section
          h2 Single Page App (SPA)
          ul
            li Web application that fits into a single web page
            li Dynamic content fetching
            li Navigability via in-page transitions rather than full page loads
            li Client-side routing

        section
          h2 Static Web App (SWA)
          blockquote(cite="http://www.staticapps.org/articles/defining-static-web-apps") Any web application that can be delivered directly to an end user's browser without server-side alteration of the HTML, CSS, or JavaScript content...rich sites that utilize technologies in the browser instead of on the server to deliver dynamic content.
          br
          small A Field Guide to Static Apps - http://www.staticapps.org

        section
          h1 The Good

        section
          h2 SPA Advantages
          ul
            li More fluid, native feeling experience
            li Progressive loading
            li More conducive to touch interactions
            li App vs. website mentality

        section
          h2 Static Advantages
          ul
            li No app server administration
            li Deployment simplicity
            li Build with what you need to know anyway HTML/CSS/JavaScript
            li Streamlined development workflow - allows focus
            li Cheap to host and scale
            li Forces a service oriented mindset

        section
          h2 Services are Everywhere
          ul
            li 11,000+ APIs on <a href="http://www.programmableweb.com/">Programmable Web</a>
            li Backend as a Service (BaaS) - <a href="http://www.firebase.com">Firebase</a>, <a href="http://www.parse.com">Parse</a>
            li Even <a target="_blank" href="https://aws.amazon.com/sdkforbrowser/">AWS</a> and <a target="_blank" href="https://developers.google.com/api-client-library/javascript/">Google</a> providing direct browser API integration
            li Build your own APIs

        section
          h2 Web Keeps Getting Better
          ul
            li Libs for SPAs - <a href="http://www.angularjs.org" target="_blank">AngularJS</a>, <a href="http://emberjs.com" target="_blank">Ember</a>, <a href="http://backbonejs.org" target="_blank">Backbone</a>
            li Modern browser ubiquity - <a href="http://thenextweb.com/insider/2014/05/01/ie11-market-share-passes-ie10-ie9-combined-chrome-cements-lead-firefox/" target="_blank">IE story improving</a>
            li Exponential browser perf improvements
            li Vibrant open source ecosystem
            li CSS3 animations
            li On the horizon - WebRTC, ES6, WebComponents, famo.us
            li Tools - Grunt, Bower
            li
              a(href="https://developers.google.com/webmasters/ajax-crawling/", target="_blank") Google AJAX crawling specification

        section
          h2 Content Focused SPAs
          ul
            li
              a(href="http://www.nytimes.com/chrome") NY Times Chrome App
            li
              a(href="http://www.yahoo.com/tech") Yahoo Tech News

        section
          h2 SPA =&gt; Future? &lt;= SWA
          a.image(href="#", target="_blank")
            img(width="590", height="394", src="images/venn_diagram.jpg", alt="Venn Diagram")

        section
          h1 The Bad

        section
          h2 SPA Disadvantages
          ul
            li SEO - search bots don't execute JavaScript
            li More complex, JavaScript hell
            li Mental shift from server to browser
            li Back button, refreshes, deep links
            li Auth

        section
          h2 Static App Disadvantages
          ul
            li API keys exposed in source code
            li Slow or rate limited APIs
            li No secure session state
            li Localhost integration, i.e. OAuth
            li Lack of JSONP or CORS support
            li APIs that don't want to be exposed to the world

        section
          h1 The Ugly
          ul
            li Browser plugins - Flash, Silverlight
            li Mobile browser capabilities still lagging - jerky animations
            li Homegrown frameworks
            li Plugin/libs bloat
            li Javascript memory leak debugging
            li Security through obfuscation

        section
          h2 Introducing Aerobatic
          ul
            li Managed cloud middle-tier platform for single page static apps
            li Build static apps but benefit from an active server working on your behalf
            li Use the browser libraries you love
            li Powered by AWS, Redis, Grunt, and Node.js

        section
          h2 Smart Hosting Modules
          ul
            li Suite of smart hosting modules
            li SEO snapshots
            li Intelligent service proxy
            li Asset delivery optimization - CDN + gzip + min + fingerprinted
            li Split test multiple versions
            li Fully integrated development environment using simulator mode
            li "grunt deploy" to the cloud
            li OAuth integration

        section
          h1 Demo!

        section
          h2 Learn More
          ul
            li <a href="http://www.aerobatic.io" target="_blank">www.aerobatic.io</a>
            li These slides online at <a href="http://slides.aerobatic.io" target="_blank">slides.aerobatic.io</a>
            li <a href="https://twitter.com/aerobaticapp">@aerobaticapp</a>
            li david@aerobatic.io
            li Wings for nimble web apps

